                " \nAGR\u00c9MENT SOUTH AFRICA\n ",
                " \n \nEcolabelling Manager\nBe an early applicant\nPretoria\nPermanent\nFull Time\nR 894,764.00 per month (All-inclusive CTC)\nEE/AA, Non EE/AA\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nIntroduction\nWe are currently recruiting for a Ecolabelling Manager to join our team. \n \nPurpose:\nTo implement and manage all the ecolabelling scheme activities.\n \nDuties & Responsibilities\n \nTechnical Responsibilities\nManage all eco ASA activities\nManage the issuance of eco ASA ecolabels\nManage the certification/ licensing of ecolabels\nConduct environmental impact analysis\nDevelop and review existing eco ASA specifications in line with the methodology adopted by Good Environmental Choice Australia (GECA), by reviewing the applicability of the GECA standards and any other applicable best-practice eco-label standards and their relevance in South Africa\nAdhere to Global Best practices when assessing products, and new schemes for potential certification holders and/or clients\nReview and update the eco ASA business model in consultation with the Technical Group Leaders\nPrepares for and leads eco ASA internal and external audits\nResponsible for all elements of new Scheme marketing\nProvides insights and educates various Stakeholders on new schemes and their impact on ASA business\nDevelops and maintains a potential client database\nDevelops and maintains a technical expert database, for the purpose of reviewing new environmentally friendly specifications\nDevelop and review specific scheme rules\nDevelop pilot programs for each of the approved specifications\nParticipates in various technical communities of ASA and provides advice on matters relating to Eco-Labelling\nImplement risk management process an procedures in the division and in the execution of applicable task\nPresents and publishes research work to relevant conferences, seminars, workshops, forums, journals, etc., under the guidance from the Research and Development Group Leader\nResearch and Development Responsibilities\nUndertakes Investigations to any developments within the built environment\nResearch the efficacy of each scheme and its impact on ASA\u2019s technical divisions and existing certificate holders or clients\nInvestigate the profitability of each scheme and report on how it is received by ASA\u2019s certificate members\nLiaise with various organizations such as GECA, research and report on best-practice ecolabelling standards and their possible relevance in South Africa\nResearch and create Marketing plans for the organizations for the targeted organizations and those in the database\nCarry Eco-Labelling Research Projects under the guidance of the Research and Development Group Leader\nInvestigate different methods of issuing ecolabels\nKnowledge\nSeek Training and develop your own skills\nSupport staff development in all technical aspects of Eco-Labelling\nSupport the development of staff, especially those that would report in this role\nAbility to develop training programmes and roll them out to various stakeholders including the technical team\nAbility to research new trends and developments and hold workshops internally for various stakeholders including the technical team\nAbility to deliver all Eco-Labelling presentations\nQuality Assurance\nSupport the implementation and adherence to Agrement Quality Assurance Policy, Procedures, and standards by\nEnsuring that technical outputs of the Eco-Labelling team are reviewed and are of high standards and ensuring credibility and success of the new schemes\nEnsure alignment of new schemes with ASA\u2019s quality assurance principles, policies, and procedures\nContribute to internal quality audits, especially in line with Eco-Labelling matters\nAd-hoc Specialization & Ad Hoc Duties\nPerform specialized functions to support various eco-labeling projects that Agrement may deem necessary, and where the incumbent may be deemed as a recognized industry expert\nPrepare technical reports to communicate the successes and criteria used for various schemes\nPerform Any Reasonable Given by the Executive Manager: Technical Services\n \nDesired Experience & Qualification\nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nDegree in Environmental science, Built Environment       \nFive (5) Years\u2019 experience as a specialist in environment specification, standards, and development of new schemes and issuing ecolabels experience (especially within a climate-conscious and green environment.\nExposure to ISO Systems\nIdeal\nHonors/Postgrad Degree\nTotal of 10 Years experience with Five (5) Years experience in a specialist role and an additional Five (5) Years\u2019 experience as a manager. \nISO 14024 Training\nISO 17065 Training\nProfessional Engineering Registration\nManagerial and Technical Competencies:\nKnowledge of PAIA, POPIA, and ASA Act\nExperience in reviewing and/or issuing of ecolabels\nKnowledge and exposure to environmental laws and regulations\nKnowledge and Understanding of QMS, environment standards ISO, SANS, and others\nKnowledge planning, execution, training, and computer skills\nKnowledge of the Built Industry, SABS Standards, and ISO standards\nProject Management\nAbility to interact with highly skilled professionals\nSkilled Analytical Mind & Data Analysis\nGeneric Competencies:\nAccuracy (Essential)\nAttention to detail (Essential)\nComputer Skills (Essential)\nCommunication Skills (verbal & written)\nConfidentiality (Essential)\nPlanning and organizing skills.\nAdministrative Skills\nTime Management Skills\nTeam Working Skills\nProblem Solving Skills\nProfessionalism\nPresentation Skills\nDocument & Record Management\n \nPackage & Remuneration\nR 894,764.00 per month (All-inclusive Cost to Company)\n \nDisclaimer\nPreference will be given to the candidates whose appointment or promotion meets the requirements for Employment Equity representativity in Agrement South Africa\n \nPlease note that correspondence will be limited to shortlisted candidates only.\n \nAgr\u00e9ment South Africa reserves the right not to make an appointment.\n \nAPPLY NOW",
                "PLANNING, MONITORING AND EVALUATION MANAGER\nPretoria\nPermanent\nFull Time\nR 760 549.00 per annum (All-inclusive CTC\nEE/AA, Non EE/AA\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nIntroduction\nWe are currently recruiting for a Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation Manager to join our team. \n \nPurpose:\nThe primary purpose of this role is to oversee ASA\u2019s planning, organizational performance, reporting, monitoring, and evaluation of ASA\u2019s projects and interventions.\n \nDuties & Responsibilities\nDevelopment of Strategic and Performance Planning:\nEnsure a strategic plan and performance plan are developed and submitted timeously to various authorities such as the Department of Public Works and other Regulatory Bodies by performing the following Duties:\nReview the ASA strategic plans and updates in line with newly formed performance targets\nCo-ordinates the gathering of information towards the review of ASA\u2019s annual performance plan and various (other) strategic documents\nCo-ordinates and ensures information are collected and tracks the success and challenges of running ASA projects\nSubmits and presents accurate performance reports on all strategic projects to various partners/stakeholders and other regulatory bodies\nEnsure Proper Risk Management Policies and procedures are adhered to\nEnsure adequate and continuous research is conducted for contribution to annual Planning and performance reports\nDrive and ensure proper management of sustainability initiatives\nConduct extensive research for Planning and Performance monitoring and evaluation\nLiaise with the Department of Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation (DPME) to Keep abreast with the Government reporting Framework\nEnsure that quarterly and annual performance is audited before submission to relevant authorities\nEnsuring Implementation of all Risk Management Policies and Procedures\nManage the quality management systems across the board\nManagement of Performance Information Monitoring and Reporting\nEstablishes a monitoring and evaluation framework within ASA, with clear goals, outcomes, outputs, processes, and indicators\nSupports the CEO, in carrying his mandate by establishing mechanisms for effective monitoring and reporting\nDevelops Standard Operating Procedures that provide guidance to various heads of divisions on how various project(s), and interventions should be managed\nAdvises divisional heads, project managers, and project specialists (Researchers, Assessors) on evidence requirements for monitoring and reporting purposes\nClarifies roles and responsibilities of all business units and reports on performance targets that have been reached and reports on both successes and challenges\nAssists various divisions within ASA by aligning their core operational activities with the ASA\u2019s strategic objectives\nMonitors and ensures that various business units perform against their strategic divisional goals and report on identified performance outages on each of the business units and/or divisions\nPresent quarterly and annual performance information to the committees, Board, and authorities\nData Management and Analysis\nKeep abreast of developments in the ASA environment in line with new products, schemes, affiliations etc.\nIdentifies strengths and weaknesses in existing processes and recommends remedial changes to optimize chances of success on all ASA\u2019s projects\nPartner with various project leaders such as Eco-Labelling Manager, Research Heads, and Technical Services Heads and monitor projects in support of the CEO\u2019s mandate\nInvestigates suitable data management systems for ASA, and recommends suitable tools for analysis\nIdentify strengths and weaknesses in existing data collection and management systems and propose solutions\nConduct Sites visits when necessary and ensure all information is verified, and verifiable for audit purposes\nQuality Assurance\nSupports the implementation and adherence to ASA\u2019s Quality Assurance Policies, Procedures, and standards by\nEnsuring that all projects within ASA are completed successfully and all remedial plans are aligned with Quality Assurance Policies and Procedures\nEnsures all projects led by ASA are of the highest quality makes recommendations to business unit heads on plans and strategies and ensures adherence to higher standards of quality as per Quality Assurance Policies, Procedures, and Standards\nReport on Identified Risks in Projects, where Quality Assurance Policies, Procedures, and Standards may have been ignored\nAd-Hoc Duties\nPerform all responsibilities which may be assigned by the CEO from time to time\n \nDesired Experience & Qualification\nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nFirst Degree in Public Administration\n5 years\u2019 experience in Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation, Environment\nIdeal\n10 years\u2019 experience in a planning Monitoring and Evaluation Environment\nHonors/Postgraduate degree\n \nManagerial and Technical Competencies:\nKnowledge and understanding of PAIA, Public Service, Records, and Archiving standards\nPOPI Act\nMonitoring and Evaluation Techniques\nBusiness Process Improvements\nStrategy Management\nReport Writing Skills\nPresentation Skills\nBudget Management Skills\nAnalytical Skills\nUnderstanding of the Built environment and disciplines\nKnowledge of standards within the Built Environment\nProject Management, Process Mapping, and Project Administration\nTechnical Report Writing\nProcess Mapping and Project Management\n \nGeneric Competencies:\nAnalytical\nAccuracy (Essential)\nAttention to detail (Essential)\nComputer Skills (Essential)\nCommunication Skills\nConfidentiality (Essential)\nPlanning and organizing skills.\nAdministrative Skills\nTime Management Skills\nTeam Working Skills\nProblem Solving Skills\nResearch skill\n \n \nPackage & Remuneration\nR 760 549.00 per annum (All-inclusive Cost to Company)\n \nDisclaimer\nPreference will be given to the candidates whose appointment or promotion meets the requirements for Employment Equity representativity in Agrement South Africa\n\n \nPlease note that correspondence will be limited to shortlisted candidates only.\n \nAgr\u00e9ment South Africa reserves the right not to make an appointment.\n \nAPPLY NOW"
