                " \nBROADBAND INFRACO\n ",
                "Broadband Infraco, is a long distance national and international optic fibre connectivity network infrastructure provider based in Radiokop, seeks to appoint a suitable candidate to the following employment opportunity:\n \nINTERNAL AND EXTERNAL JOB ADVERTISEMENT\nADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT: SCM (PERMANENT)\n \nKey Responsibilities:\nReporting to the Manager: Performance and Planning, the incumbent will:\nAdministrative Support\nAttend to enquiries from Business Units requesting to procure goods and services. Assist Supply Chain Management staff with general office duties upon request. Coordinate and schedule meeting appointments as requested. Take minutes during departmental meetings.\nAssist with distribution / preparation of documents / correspondence. Management of business stationary. Stationary inventory usage control. Purchasing and maintenance of stationary stock level. Capture and update inventory list on pastel. Produce the monthly usage report for Finance manager. Report to internal and external customers enquiries. Travel and accommodations bookings for procurement department.\nProcurement Support\nProcure business cards for Business Units Personnel. Correspond with vendors regarding their database registration and any other procurement enquiries. Create Purchase Requisitions for Supply Chain Department. Request for quotations. Issue of purchase Orders and get Procurement manager to approve. Closing of tenders. Issue tender numbers sequentially. Record the tender status on the departmental board. Record contract and alert contract manager about the expiry date. Maintain contracts documentation, track and follow documentation through the contracting processes to ensure completion. Verify delivered goods according to Purchase Order. Contact vendors for any variations on goods delivered.\nDatabase Management and record Keeping\nScan, load record contract files to Shared drive. Keep records and database updated on a regular basis and ensure system compliance and procurement policy is adhered to. File service\u2019 Tax clearance certificate, RFQ files and contracts files as per check list. Send reminders to service provider to update their Tax clearance. Archive unsuccessful bids and old contract files. File the RFQ files and contracts files as per check list. Maintenance of vendor records. Review requisitions for completeness and accuracy, follow up on discrepancies with the initiating department and identify available suppliers for each requisition item. Maintenance of Supplier Database. Coordinate the accreditation process of service providers. Maintain procedures of monitoring database performance.\n \nQualification and Experience:\n\u2022 Diploma in Administrative Management.\n\u2022 Must have at least 2 \u2013 3 years administrative experience preferably in finance department. Knowledge of procurement processes and database management.\n\u2022 Computer literacy, Microsoft office suite \u2013 Intermediate.\n \nApplications and a comprehensive CV to be e-mailed to jobs@infraco.co.za\n \nEnquiries should be directed to Ms. Nompumelelo Mtsweni \u2013 Contact Details: 011 235 1612\n(Office Hours)\n \nClosing Date: 09 November 2023.\n \nBroadband Infraco reserves the right not to make an appointment or to make a temporary appointment in accordance with the current organizational requirements. Appointment is subject to verification of the applicant\u2019s qualifications and reference checking.\nApplications received after the closing date will not be considered.\nCorrespondence will be entered into with short-listed applicants only. If you have not heard from us within 4 weeks, you should consider your application unsuccessful.\nPlacement will be in accordance with the Company\u2019s Employment Equity Plan. Persons with disabilities are encouraged to apply.",
                "Broadband Infraco, is a long distance national and international optic fibre connectivity network infrastructure provider based in Radiokop, seeks to appoint a suitable candidate to the following employment opportunity:\n \nINTERNAL AND EXTERNAL JOB ADVERTISEMENT\n \nGENERAL MANAGER: SUPPLY CHAIN MANAGEMENT (PERMANENT)\n \nKey Responsibilities:\nReporting to the Chief Financial Officer, the incumbent will:\n\u2022 Provide support to SCM managers in ensuring compliance to SCM policies, process, procedures and the Legislation across the organisation and by other stakeholders and ensure alignment of strategy to all relevant legislation i.e., PPPFA, PFMA, Treasury Regulations, companies Act etc.\n \nQualification and Experience:\n\u2022 Relevant Commercial Degree in Supply Chain Management.\n\u2022 Honours degree or MBA would be an added advantage.\n\u2022 Minimum 8 years Senior Management experience in supply chain management, Minimum 5 years in the Public Sector.\n\u2022 Experience in the ICT environment or a major infrastructure company.\n\n\u2022 Detailed knowledge of legislation PPPFA, PFMA, BBBEE etc and CIPS accreditation will be an added advantage.\n\u2022 Analyse the 5-year Broadband Infraco Corporate Plan to determine the strategic direction for Supply Chain Management.\n\u2022 Develop the competitive enterprise and supplier development strategy that is aligned to Broadband Infraco\u2019 s mandate and direct the implementation thereof.\n\u2022 Develop BBBEE policy in alignment with ICT Charter and direct the implementation and compliance across the organisation and to improve the overall company BBBEE score card.\n\u2022 Establish partnerships with large businesses to foster skills development of Black Women Owned, Black Youth Owned, People with Disabilities and Black Owned Entities.\n\u2022 Establish partnerships with academic institutions for business skills as part of supplier development, the Bid/Tender issuing and evaluation, the management of EXCOPS and Tender Committee reports.\n\u2022 Provide input to the Annual report to Shareholders.\n\u2022 Develop Monthly reports to EXCO.\n \n \nApplications and a comprehensive CV to be e-mailed to jobs@infraco.co.za\n \nEnquiries should be directed to Ms. Nompumelelo Mtsweni \u2013 Contact Details: 011 235 1612 (Office Hours)\n \nClosing Date: 21 November 2023.\n \nBroadband Infraco reserves the right not to make an appointment or to make a temporary appointment in accordance with the current organizational requirements. Appointment is subject to verification of the applicant\u2019s qualifications and reference checking.\nApplications received after the closing date will not be considered.\nCorrespondence will be entered into with short-listed applicants only. If you have not heard from us within 4 weeks, you should consider your application unsuccessful.\nPlacement will be in accordance with the Company\u2019s Employment Equity Plan. Persons with disabilities are encouraged to apply."
