                " \nESKOM\n ",
                " \n \nMIDDLE MANAGER REPORTING GX GROUP CAPITAL MEGAWATT PARK X1\nVacancy type: External/Internal\nTask Grade : M17\nArea of Specialization : To drive the development and design of implementation strategies for the performance management function and to give assurance to the business on performance aligned to strategic and operational goals\nDepartment : Capital Execution Assurance (CEA)\nBusiness Unit : Capital Execution Assurance (CEA)\nLocation : South Africa (Gauteng)\nReference Number : 50086036GM\nClosing Date : 11/24/2023\n \nMinimum Requirements\n\u2022Qualification(s):\nB Degree/B Tech National Higher Diploma/Advanced Diploma in Business Management/Business Administration/Commerce/ Human Sciences at NQF7 with 360 credits\n\n\u2022Related Minimum Experience:\n7 years in Reporting methodologies, techniques, processes performance measurement\n \nSkills and Competencies\nLeadership\n\u2022Business acumen\n\u2022Building effective teams\n\u2022Change leadership\n\u2022Embracing diversity\n\u2022Results orientation\n\u2022People management\n\u2022Strategy alignment\n\nBehavioral\n\u2022Business leadership\n\u2022Continuous improvement\n\u2022Integrity\n\u2022Honesty\n\u2022Trustworthiness\n\u2022Professionalism\n\n\nKnowledge\n\u2022Risk management\n\u2022Negotiation and project management\n\u2022Performance management reporting\n\u2022Enterprise risk management processes\n\u2022Financial analysis and management reporting\n\u2022Shareholder and industry analysis\n\nSkill\n\u2022Analytical\n\u2022Change management\n\u2022Systems thinking\n\u2022Processing\n\u2022Management\n\u2022Business Intelligence\n\u2022Report writing\n\u2022Understanding complex concept\n\u2022Communication and engagement\n\u2022Customer orientation\n\u2022Judgement and decision making\n\nAttributes\n\u2022Self-Motivation\n\u2022Emotional Intelligence\n\u2022Prioritization and Time Management\n\u2022Problem Solving\n \nKey Responsibilities\n\u2022Direct performance reporting and data integrity monitoring.\n\u2022Define and implement strategies, policies and procedures.\n\u2022Lead the performance management portfolio team.\n\u2022Manage stakeholder relationships.\n\n\nFOR ASSISTANCE WITH THIS ADVERT, PLEASE EMAIL recruitmentgcd@eskom.co.za\n\n\u201cIf you have not been contacted within 28 days after the closing date of this advertisement, please accept that your application was unsuccessful.\u201d\n\u201cEskom is committed to equality, employment equity, and diversity. In accordance with the employment equity plan of Eskom and its employment equity goals and targets, preference may be given, but is not limited, to candidates from under-represented designated groups.  Eskom reserves the right not to make an appointment to the posts as advertised.\nCandidates with disabilities are encouraged to apply for positions.\u201d\n \nEskom is committed to providing a smoke-free environment for its employees and visitors at the workplace\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nSENIOR ADVISOR ELECTRICAL COMPLIANCE (GENERATION) LETHABO POWER STATION\nVacancy type: External/Internal\nTask Grade : G15\nArea of Specialization : To provide the organization with objective assurance on hazardous location compliance to statutory requirements and technical expertise by providing direction and guidance on the testing of electrical equipment and issuance of certificate of compliance\nDepartment : Maintenance\nBusiness Unit : Lethabo Power Station\nLocation : South Africa (Free State)\nReference Number : 50685810RS/LET\nClosing Date : 11/24/2023\n \nMinimum Requirements\n\nQualification(s):\n\u2022 B Tech/National Higher Diploma in Electrical/Mechanical Engineering at NQF 7 with 360 credits\nPlus\n\u2022 Master Installation Electrical Registration\n\nExperience\n\u2022 5 years\u2019 Power Plant and experience in an Electrical environment\n \nSkills and Competencies\n\nSkills\n\u2022 Communication\n\u2022 Computer literacy\n\u2022 Supervisory\n\u2022 Driver\u2019s licence\n\nKnowledge\n\u2022 Basic safety, health, environment (SHE)\n\u2022 Plant safety regulations authorised coach\n\u2022 Registered with the Department of Labour as Master Installation Electrician\n\u2022 Advanced Hazardous location training competency certificate\n \nKey Responsibilities\n\u2022 Provide hazardous location (HazLoc) compliance assurance\n\u2022 Ensure equipment and employee safety\n\u2022 Conduct quality control inspection\n\u2022 Provide hazardous location on job training\n\u2022 Investigate recurring defects\n\u2022 Assist and advise relevant employees on maintaining hazardous location compliance\n\u2022 Attend hazardous location related meetings\n\u2022 Coordinate and control allocated team\n\n\n** FOR ASSISTANCE WITH THIS ADVERT, PLEASE EMAIL **\nrecruitmentgx@eskom.co.za\n\n\u201cIf you have not been contacted within 28 days after the closing date of this advertisement, please accept that your application was unsuccessful.\u201d\n \n\u201cEskom is committed to equality, employment equity, and diversity. In accordance with the employment equity plan of Eskom and its employment equity goals and targets, preference may be given, but is not limited, to candidates from under-represented designated groups. Eskom reserves the right not to make an appointment to the posts as advertised.\nCandidates with disabilities are encouraged to apply for positions.\u201d\n \nEskom is committed to providing a smoke-free environment for its employees and visitors at the workplace.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                "TECHNICIAN PTM AND C ELECTRICAL, LINES ENGINEERING SERVICES CIVIL, SUBSTATION CIVIL AND ELECTRICAL X8 SIMMERPAN, TX GERMISTON AND MEGAWATT PARK\nVacancy type: External/Internal\nTask Grade : T11\nArea of Specialization : To provide technical services for engineering designs and asset care.\nDepartment : Engineering\nBusiness Unit : Engineering\nLocation : South Africa (Gauteng)\nReference Number : 50827515MM\nClosing Date : 11/24/2023\nMinimum Requirements\n\nQualification(s):\nNational Diploma / National N Diploma Engineering at NQF 6 with Credits 240\n\nExperience:\nP1 & P2 Practical Training\n\nSkills and Competencies\n\n1) Behavioural :\n\u2022 Integrity\n\u2022 Trustworthy, ethical\n\u2022 Customer focused\n\n2) Leadership :\n\u2022 Team player\n\n3) Knowledge :\n\u2022 Power plant system and technology knowledge\n\u2022 Design codes and standards\n\u2022 Engineering theory knowledge\n\u2022 Knowledge of relevant processes, procedures, policies, guidelines and legislation\n\n4) Skill :\n\u2022 Engineering design skills\n\u2022 Technical problem solving skills\n\u2022 Analytical skills\n\u2022 Communication skills\n\u2022 Presentation skills\n\u2022 Technical report writing\n\u2022 Safety consciousness\n \nKey Responsibilities\n1. Provision of technical services.\n2. Professional designs for refurbishments, modification and new build projects.\n\n3. Contributing to the integrity of the asset base.\n4. Delivering standardised outputs.\n5. Consulting on discipline related issues.\n\n\n** FOR ASSISTANCE WITH THIS ADVERT, PLEASE EMAIL:\nrecruitmenttx@eskom.co.za\n\n\u201cIf you have not been contacted within 28 days after the closing date of this advertisement, please accept that your application was unsuccessful.\u201d\n\u201cEskom is committed to equality, employment equity, and diversity. In accordance with the employment equity plan of Eskom and its employment equity goals and targets, preference may be given, but is not limited, to candidates from under-represented designated groups.  Eskom reserves the right not to make an appointment to the posts as advertised.\nCandidates with disabilities are encouraged to apply for positions.\u201d\n\n\nEskom is committed to providing a smoke-free environment for its employees and visitors at the workplace.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE",
                "OFFICER FINANCIAL ACCOUNTING X1\nVacancy type: External/Internal\nTask Grade : T12\nArea of Specialization : To provide a professional reporting and accounting support service to ensure compliance with international financial reporting standards (IFRS), applicable legislation, Eskom policies and procedures in support of sound financial control and discipline.\nDepartment : Financial Accounting\nBusiness Unit : Tutuka Power Station\nLocation : South Africa (Mpumalanga)\nReference Number : Gx50100629TL/TUT\nClosing Date : 11/24/2023\n \nMinimum Requirements\n\nQualification(s):\n\u2022 National Diploma/ National N Diploma in Financial\nAccounting/ Finance at NQF 6 with 240  credits\n\u2022 Related Minimum Experience:\n3 years\u2019 Experience in financial accounting\n \nSkills and Competencies\n\u2022 Behavioral\n\u2022 Accountability\n\u2022 Influence and persuasion\n\u2022 Integrity\n\u2022 Professionalism\n\n\u2022 Leadership:\n\u2022 Team player\n\u2022 Motivating teams\n\u2022 Coaching\n\u2022 Mentoring\n\n\u2022 Knowledge:\n\u2022 Budget and forecasting (Level 3)\n\u2022 Closing/Consolidation (level 3)\n\u2022 External reporting (Level 3)\n\u2022 Financial and accounting (level 3)\n\u2022 Financial analysis and reporting ( Level 3)\n\u2022 Financial forecasting and projections (Level 3)\n\u2022 Financial information compilation( Level 3)\n\u2022 Information interpretation (Level  3)\n\u2022 Financial risk assessment (Level 3)\n\u2022 Financial systems (Level 3)\n\u2022 General ledger maintenance (Level 3)\n\u2022 Internal control (level 3)\nKey Responsibilities\n\u2022 Provide statutory reporting packs and schedules.\n\u2022 Monitor general ledger, tax compliance, sundry debtors and retention management.\n\u2022 Ensure foreign exchange coordination and hedge accounting.\n\u2022 Maintain stakeholder management and facilitate controls.\n\u2022 Supervise employees in the functional area.\n\n\nFOR ASSISTANCE WITH THIS ADVERT, PLEASE EMAIL\nrecuitmentgx@eskom.co.za\n\nIf you have not been contacted within 28 days after the closing date of this advertisement, please accept that your application was unsuccessful.\u201d\n \n\u201cEskom is committed to equality, employment equity, and diversity. In accordance with the employment equity plan of Eskom and its employment equity goals and targets, preference may be given, but is not limited, to candidates from under-represented designated groups.  Eskom reserves the right not to make an appointment to the posts as advertised.  Candidates with disabilities are encouraged to apply for positions.\u201d\n \nEskom is committed to providing a smoke-free environment for its employees and visitors at the workplace                   \n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE"
